-- China to curb hot money inflows disguised as FDI
-- 
-- Mon Nov 15, 2010 10:08pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/11/16/us-china-economy-investment-idUSTRE6AF0NC20101116

 

 BEIJING  (Reuters) - China will restrict hot money inflows disguised as foreign direct investment, Commerce Ministry spokesman Yao Jian said on Tuesday. 

 China's foreign exchange regulator has recently stepped up efforts to curb speculative money inflows fanned by loose monetary policy in the United States. (Reporting by Aileen Wang and  Simon Rabinovitch ; Editing by Jacqueline Wong)